# Optional override for the socket.io websocket target. Leave blank.
#
# By default the SPA opens the WebSocket against its own origin
# (`new WebSocket("/socket.io/...")`), which keeps the connection
# same-origin with the API and lets the httpOnly fa_auth cookie ride
# the upgrade. Both production hostnames (flashaware.com and
# lightning-risk-api.fly.dev) are served by the same Fly machine, so
# same-origin WS works on either.
#
# Set this ONLY if you split the SPA off to a host that does NOT
# proxy /socket.io/* to the API — and be aware that cross-origin
# WebSocket cannot use the cookie. You'd need to hand the JWT in via
# socket.io's `auth.token` (server still accepts that as a fallback).
# The cookie posture is strictly better; prefer same-origin hosting.
VITE_WS_URL=
